so i stink at updating this.


an update will come later today.



k bye =)

Yeah, I know I know, I don't update this thing anymore. 
But i think i'm going to start back up with updating this.

Well, summer is almost done. 
That's fucking crazyyyy! And my senior year is already here, 
time freaking flies. This is no joke crazy. 
I'm really excited, but i'm scared at the same time. 

We had our first football game of the year yesterday, 
and we won! Our dance was pretty good =) Great Job Girls! 
It's a great way to start off the season. 

Dance Team is going great, I love the team. 
I'm excited for the season even more now that like schools getting back in sesson.
That just means competition seasons starting, and i can't wait to learn our dances!

JAZZ DANCE= ADDICTED BY KELLY CLARKSON
POM DANCE = "BAD" THEME (basically it has songs w/ bad in it ? get it? hahaha)
HOMECOMING DANCE= you'll just have to wait and see for that one. =)

Let's see... boys. YEAH you all confuse me.
End of story w/ that one. 

Work is going okay i guess. I don't really work that much, but it's still decent. 
Today was crazyyy at work tho. SSOOOO MANY people came in at once... listen to this...
a party of 20,
a party of 6,
then random parties of 2-6 kept coming in. 
I was freaking out, i've never worked when its that busy before.
And i'm not joking either. 
And then my manager told me take this party of four over to the booth, but rob got it. So then my manager said take this party of 6 to that table and rob will be happy to get it. So i seat them there, 2 min later rob freakin comes yelling at me, and my manager saw him, so my manager appologized.

Because see there is a rule that the waiters n shit can't yell at us. 
We're doing our job seating people, especially if our managers tell us to put them at a certain table. I was about to cry. It was crazy there. 
But when i left, my manager complimented me on how well i worked and stuff today. and he told me he wouldn't forget it either. =) so that kinda cheered me up a lil. 

So theres a few concerts coming up that i'm really excited to go to! 
We haveeee... 
Gym Class Heroes - Sept 22nd
New Found Glory/Cartel/The Early NOvember- Oct 13
Hellogoodbye/Dave Melillo/Cute is What We Aim For- Oct 26
Panic at The Disco/Jacks Mannequin- November 21

woooo! I can't wait i love concerts <3

Well I think i'll stop now, 
so leave me some comments, 
and i'll probally post an entry w/ pictures later 

PEACE!

So like i haven't updated this shit in forever man.


Everythings been going pretty sweet man. 

Florida was so much funn! I loved it. I miss it so much. Competition for nationals was a great experience, and I want to go back again next year. Hopefully we can. Cuz we could kick some ass =]
Like we didn't move on or nething, but we seriously did our dances SO good. Best we've ever done them pretty much. So many memories were made there no lie. Those girls are like a part of my family now. =]

Yesterday was the Starting line/gatsby's american dream/cartel/copeland/the suicide pact concert.It was really good except for Copeland. Holy crap i almost fell asleep man! lksadfjl;aksdjflsdakjf The lead singer seemed fabulous. It was fun I went with Mike Skelly, Ameer, Margaret, Brandon and Danny? lol . It was funnn! Ahh i love the starting line, and i'm like in love with cartel now. The suicide pact was sweet, and gatsbys was sweet too dude. 

School has been going okay and such i guess you can say. It's the same old school shit i guess. My grades n such are good. So i'm happy. 

Dance team is almost over, I'm getting sad =[, but next year is going to be a blast i can already tell. It's my last year next year AHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH> Oh myyyy i can't think about that man. 

Everything else is pretty good? Mas o Menos i guess. 

March 24th- PANIC AT THE DISCO/The Academy Is/HELLOgoodBYE! jd;askljsdf YAYY
March 25th MY BIRTHDAY WHAT NOW FOO
April 20th- FALLOUTBOY/AAR/FFTL/HH =] YEAHH BOII

class is almost over. 

peace out man.

Dudddeee I haven't updated this thing since before Christmas break......

A LOT has happened since then. 

- Christmas was good, I went to chicago to see the family. 
- I went to go see the Audition/A second too late/Spitalfield in concert
- Uhhh Hung out with some cool people like julie becky leesh nick and lance and ross and yeahh man. 
- Had lots and lots of dance! 
- School started back up, had a game danced etc etc. 
- I had practice every day for like two weeks. wasn't bad. 
- Had competition on saturday, and we got 4th place in our division out of 14 teams! we weren't many points away from getting 3rd.2nd.1st place man. It was nuts. 
- Sadly garrett passed away =[. R.I.P 
- Nationals is in 3 weeks. FLORIDA BABY! We will kick ass. 
- We have compeition next saturday in Birch Run and I expect to see all of you there. ;]
- Hmm things are confusing. 
- My dad bought a new computer it's a sony. It's not in yet, but it should be soon, I hopeeee!
- I bought tickets for the Fall Out Boy Concert April 20th. Mine/Andreas seats are sweet. 
- I'm going to see The Starting Line in Feb., Panic! At the Disco/TheAcademy Is/Hellogoodbye in March, Motion City Soundtrack April 2nd, The Early November/ Chiodos April 13th, tehn Fall Out boy on the 20th. 




i would type more but class is almsot over. 
peace out.

So Nick told me i never update anymore, cuz i don't. 

Lately i haven't really had time for much, which sucks. 

Basically i've been dancing dancing dancing and school, and yeah stuff like that. 
everythings okay now i guess you can say. 

I'm getting tickets to two concerts sooon. i'm super excited. 
and their cheap so thats sweet. 

The thing
I just like realized the other day was that by next year this time... my senior year is going to be half over. WTF I was just like a freshman last year (literally 2 years ago but you catch my rift) Thats really scary i'll be applying to colleges, busy with dance team, and all that jazz. I'll be like out of high school in a lil over a year its scaryyyyyyy. :( EEP!

I haven't had a real update in a while.

I just haven't really felt like it cuz no one really comments anymore. 

I dunno lately I've felt emotionaly distressed. I haven't really told anyone that, cuz well, lately some people just haven't seemed like they've wanted to listen to me. Things are getting better though I guess you can say. I really miss some of my friends. Some I hardly get the chance to talk to and or see and it really sucks. I hate it when some people will tell me AMY WE HAVEN'T HUNG OUT AND SO LONG! then like make plans without me, while I am stuck at home sitting on my ass doing nothing ? Oh well, doesn't bother me too much. 

Dance has been pretty good. We had our extravaganza on friday. Thanks to all that came =], it means a lot that you guys went... well those that could make it! It went pretty well. Monday we're learning our pom dance, and i'm over excited. 

Florida in Two Months. I'm ExCITED! 

Tara and I are going to be making up sweet dances, and I'm EXCITED. 

I was going to dance with Mariah Carey on thursday/try out for that whole thing., but do to techniqal difficulties. . . I'm not. =[ booooooo. 

Sara and Steph were flipping awesome in the crucible. 
It makes me wish that my mom would have let me try out for TAPP my freshie year. 

I saw Harry Potter today! =]
I liked it a lotttttttttt. 
But the ending kinda disappointed me. 

There was this cute waiter at Pancho Villas. Hmmm. I should go there more ofter hahahahhaha. 

I am naming the most random things right now. 
I'm stupid lol . 

UGh I'm Tired. but i dont want to go to bed... because NO SCHOOOL! YEahh.


Well i guess i'm done cuz i suck at life hahahha. 

Later Loves.

Howdy. well things have been claming down i guess you can say. Dance Team- We had our competition on Saturday, and we placed 4th overall out of 7 teams. Which isn't bad. The head of UDA told our coach she thought we would have gotten 2nd or 3rd place, but oh well. lol I'm still really proud of us, our dance looked really good. I heard Ike (they won first) used their Nationals Routine from last year... so no wonder they won lol. The head of uda said that we've gotten SOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO much better, she complimented us so much. And she never gives compliments, so that right there alone, is a huge compliment. We worked really hard, and In my mind we kicked some major ass. =] GREAT JOB GIRLS <3! We looked so like mad at the world out there, it was interesting. I really don't know what else i've been doing besides school and dance lol. OMG OKAY! READY? of course you are. So you all know how mr.french grades rediculously? So i had a d (in danger of failing) in his class, when i get a's and b's in english usually. I brought my notebook into him the other day, and OMG. IT RAISED MY GRADE ALL THE WAY UP TO A C/C+ =] you have no idea how happy that makes me y0. Wow, i read steph-a-roo's last entry, and it seriously made me sad/scared. WE ARE ALMOST HALF WAY THROUGH OUR JUNIOR YEAR. Pretty soon we're going to be applying for scholorships and colleges, paying for senior things, and entering our senior year. I really don't want next year to come, because I don't want all my amazing senior friends now to leave (like my bffe's julie and becky and raffi, and all the leadership people, and people like kevin, chris, joe, chris, jamie, adam, etc) It's so scary to think that the first day of school next year, they won't be there. =[ Erg, I better keep in touch with all these kids, if i don't man. I don't know what i'd do. Then seriously it's going to be so scary this summer already we have to take SENIOR PICTURES. WOAH. I remember thinkin my freshman year like dude thats so far away, and now it's like almost here. I remember in like 4th grade, we wrote a paper about what it would be like when we graduate, and I said CARS WOULD FLY haha wow. But man, that really makes me sad. =[ OYE I'm freeeezing in my house its so cold. Man, somethings feel like their falling apart =[ Anyone have some permenent glue? heh Well right now this is all i can think of..! Leave me some comments. Later playas (P.S. Listen to BEEP by the pussycat dolls) it's so funny HAHHAAA

Well Well Well. I haven't updated in a long time.... Chicago was a lot of fun. I got t o hang out with my family. It's always fun hangin iwth my cousins and such. They can always help me have a good ol time. I went to navy pier and such. It was fun. Brit and Kim are sweet cousins! For shizzle. Dance Camp was Sweet. Thursday----- (Last Week) We met up at mott, and had to take pictures for coach writght. Then we headed over to the wcc and practiced. We went to the Hotel and Chilled and swam. Then we went out to DINNER! lol At the Rainforest Cafe at GreatLakesCrossing. It was so much fun. Steph, Vroom, Lauren, Catie and Stina are so funny. Our dinners were yummy. Then we went back to the hotel, chilled and swam somemore and had our candle light. Awww yay, I love those girls. Steph is hilarious. Then we all just went to beddd. Friday- We got all spiffy and ready, then we all went to Timmy Ho ho's! (Tim Hortans). yummy. The car i was in (lauren's with tara juliet candice and me) we got lost lol. Then we headed over to OU! We unpacked, and I saw Ms.Geri! Yay! Then we got situated in our rooms, practiced, had pizza, then Lauren Me Coach and Vroom had a meeting for camp with all the other coaches and capitains. We put people into their A routines. I was in the Level 4 Team Routine with Vroom, Catie, Tara and Stina. It's sweet for shizz. Then we had homeroutine evaluations. Wow, Chippewah was so good, and so were some other teams. We did pretty good, everyone was singing and clapping around with our music! Ross, B, Jill, Krystal and Mike all came. It twas sweet. Then we all "went to bed" Catie and I talked till 2:30 YAY! I love Catios>! Also we got the "on the ball" award from the UDA staff. That's sucha good thing to get. Saturday--Got up early. Booo, then i went to All Stars. I knew i wasn't going to make it, but Hey! It's worth a try! Then everyone came, and we did stretches, reviewed a routine and stuff. After Lunch i had another meeting and we put people in their B Routines! I was in Level 3/4 Kick Shake It! With ms.Tara Mace! She's so funny. It's a really killer kick line. It killed my legs for sure. Then after we had a picture party and technique and such. Then at dinner time we had another meeting, and put people into their C Routines. I was in Level Four Hip Hop with Vroom and Stina to Hey bitty! It's so freaking sweeeeeeet. Heck yes. then we did ICE CREAM AND CAKE! and Peanut butter jelly and other stuff and headed to beddd. Sunday- Hmmm nothing relaly exciting. Reviewed all of our routines, and then we had A Routine/All Star Evaluations. My mommy and pappiiii came :) YAY!So did ross and b. That was nice of them :). Vroom, Tara, Stina, Catie and I got blue ribbons for the team routine. cuz we're sweet. Then Tara and I practiced our Kick, and stina and vroom and i practiced our hiphop.Then i had a meeting with coach, lauren and vroom in vrooms room.We talked till 1:30. We couldn't stop laughing. Then I came back , and Catios was sleeping so i just went to bed. Monday-- LAST DAY OF CAMP. We performed our B and C routines, and got evaluated. I got all blue ribbons (which is the best you can get sweeet). Then we did our a routines again, drill downs, ice cream and cake. Then we did awards. We qualified for nationals! =] Vroom, Lauren and I also got invited to go to the Macy's day parade for thanksgiving and perform since we're captains. Yay! i doubt i'll do it tho. Then Ms. Kristina got the All Star Award! YAY Then camp was like over.... Camp was awesome. I got a lot closer to a lot of the new girls and i love them! So many hillarious things happened, and I'm a lot closer to everyone. We have a great team this year. These girls have a lot of heart for the game, and i really hope they don't lose it. If they do, I 'll be kicking some butt ! =] JayKay. But to be on a team like this you need to have the heart to succeed. Girls that have come and gone on the team, have the heart for dance just not the dance team. Dance teams a part of my life and i wouldn't trade it for anything. This team this year, is going to go far and do great things. Don't doubt us, cuz then we'll doubt you. We make the commitment and not the excuses. We're the lovers and fighters of dance. We will be kicking ass this year. So when you hearsome one talking about the WM Magix, be like oh yeah, their kick ass =] And don't think i'm trying to be cocky about the dance team saying we're sweet and all, because i know/ have a feeling that during the season... u guys will be like whos that? wait WHAT? WOAH THATS OUR DANCE TEAM. Seriously. Don't think i'm psyco for saying all that either. Ask anyone on the team this year. They will most likely say the same things just in different wordings. Feburary 3rd-6th. I'm Jacked... Are you? Monday? I slept till about 8 then ate dinner? lol Tuesday? I had dance class, then becky and julie came over and then we went to beckys house and hung with ashton and sean. Nice parking joob beckyyy ahha. Weds-Dance Team, Practiced with steph, home, doctors, beckys house for a sleepover with julie. It was a lot of fun..! =] So i fall alseep? Okay... then i wake up and I hear this Jamacian voice talking and then laughing, and he keeps repeating the SAME STUFF> I was like wtfffff. (the tv was on, but i was to outta it to notice) Then I looked at the tv, and the 3rd harry potter movie was still on and it was on the menu part for special features. Geeze it freaked me out. Then Julie and I did lil mike's and ted's makeup and hair for ozzfest cuz we're sweet. Then julie dropped becky off at mott, and i went with julie to get a work permit. Woo.
